children.subject: Undergraduate entry into CS graduate level courses is by permission of the instructor.  The criteria for that permission isn't necessarily figured out until close to the first day of lecture when space and demand is more clear.
also, what are the enrollment criteria this time for 280? i hear last time it was offered, an A/A+ was required in 189/194-26 for undergraduates to enroll. is this the case this time too?

history.content:
While we understand there is significant interest from undergraduate students (who make up the entire waitlist for c280 at this time) to take this graduate level course, it is highly unlikely that a larger room will be requested to accommodate students other than the graduate students towards which this course is aimed.  This means that the largest the class will be would be 108 students.


If Prof Darrell wanted to request a larger room we would submit a request but since the course is scheduled at one of the 3 most popular timeslots, it is somewhat unlikely one would be available on campus.

children.subject: There is no new information since last time a similar version of this question was asked.  See earlier answers.  While the enrollment limit will likely move to closer to 108 as the start of class approaches, the great majority of undergraduate students who are really interested in taking this class and are currently on the waitlist will not get in regardless of whether the final enrollment limit is 90 or 108.  Graduate students still have over a month to decide to enroll before undergraduate enrollment is likely to be considered.  Undergraduate students who are waitlisted for 280 need a backup plan in case it doesn't work out.

Would it be possible to expand the enrollment to the maximum capacity of the room? I know of quite a few undergraduates who are really interested in taking this class, but who may not get in depending on the capacity.

history.content: Would it be possible to increase the capacity for CS C280, seeing as there is a lot of demand for the course? It's in 306 Soda as of now, with about 57 people on the waitlist, but only 36 more spots open.
